flowRoot.flowPara: When a transfer is done you'll get a notification to be able to act upon it.
If Transfers is closed during a running transfer, you'll get a icon in the message tray with the currently running transfers.
When all the transfers are done the tray icon should go away.

This guy is waiting in line. If he's a small file a longer running file will get him pass through, based on some negotiation. The reasoning behind not doing parallel transfers is that they will slow each other down.
After files are finished they line up here for a certain while before going into "previous transfers". Maybe this depends on if you looked at it or not?
The transfers will always show approximate times, such as "About 1 Hour",
Something went wrong with this transfer. Maybe the connection broke, maybe the disk is full? You can kickstart it again. Maybe it tries again every once in a while?
Transfers will do it's best to create thumbnails for transfers. EXIF info, nautilus thumbs, web cache?
